article.headline: Radford 71, Coastal Carolina 67
article.story: RADFORD, Va. -- Chris McEachin scored 19 points and Artsiom Parakhouski added 16 points and 18 rebounds to lead Radford past Coastal Carolina 71-67 in overtime on Monday night. The Highlanders (14-10, 11-2 Big South Conference) scored the first five points in overtime and held on to win their fifth straight game and 10th in the last 11 outings. Radford led 47-36 with 11:46 left in regulation, but the Chanticleers (10-15, 4-9) used an 18-6 run to pull ahead 54-53. After McEachin hit a layup to give the Highlanders a 60-59 lead with 15 seconds left, Joseph Harris made the second of two free throws with 1 second on the clock to force overtime. This was only the second single-digit victory by the Highlanders this season. Kenny Thomas added 12 points for Radford. Dexter Moore paced the Chanticleers with 22 points and Harris added 14 points and 14 rebounds.
